caption: Amazing first dinner in NOLA! Great food. Friendly staff. Amazing ambiance in the outdoor courtyard. Will definitely be back.

Not sure if it should be a 3 or a 4... The Good, - food was great, the service at table was very good ! The bad. - NOT all the menú is available during COVID, I’d say it’s pretty limited. The Ugly, - we were at the entrance, waiting for a host to come back, 3 employees passed by and no one said Hi!.... a bit disappointing.

Wonderful experience. This is why you come to New Orleans. Excellent food, fun and friendly service. It's the collection of chefs and restaurants like this that make the quarter special. Thank you. PS. Cornbread is so good, I ordered some to take home to mom. It's a must.
Great atmosphere and food!

Creative craft cocktails as always, but seemed like a few may have been a bit diluted; was wondering if the bartender was overshaking, or if the ice was too small/not cold enough. Lily is a great server- very friendly and knowledgeable
Love the ambience😌
The fried oysters were delicious and so are the sweet potatoes. You probably should reserve ahead of time and try to score the tables and the way back which are intimate and romantic.
High end cuisine in a casual and stylish atmosphere. A great first meal in Nola.
It was great! Food was good. Drinks were good. Atmosphere was good. Service is fantastic! Great place for a quiet lunch or dinner.
Awesome lunch spot !! All sandwiches are excellent !

Loved, loved, loved our dinner here - we were very impressed with the pork belly and the gulf fish, but the marinated beets blew us away. The kids were so happy with the pappardelle con ragù and the pots de crème au chocolat. We sat outside in the courtyard and it was magical
Absolutely loved this place!! You have to try the house made cola with fernet! Just unbelievable!
Such a unique place to eat...if they have the Chefs surprise...I think that is the name of it...try it...I think it was 5 courses ans amazing...you'll be glad you ate here!!!
Watered down drinks and they feel it’s their business to interject into a couples relationship

The burger and fries were great. Also order the pork and cabbage ravioli. Both were great. The burger was generous portion and cooked as ordered. The ravioli was great, but it could have been a larger portion for the price. A small side of veggies would have been perfect.

Outstanding dinner, drinks and service.   Ordered the Dealer’s Choice, chef chooses your four course meal.   If you are a foodie, you will love this selection.   You don’t know what’s coming but know it is wonderful.   The waiter asks if there are any food restrictions when you order.

We ordered the dealers choice. Each item that came out was excellent and I have never tasted something quite as delicious in my life. My girlfriend and I were looking for unique New Orleans cuisine and stumbled across this restaurant while heading towards the church down the street. From the music to the atmosphere to the excellent service from all staff members, we throughly enjoyed the entire experience through and through. We will be returning when we come back to the area!
Cozy little gastro pub. Very nice setting, intimate but casual enough for a nice weekday evening

Absolutely wonderful! I had the best Wasabi crusted fish I have ever eaten here! The depth of flavors developed in the sauces, broths and dressings was completely mouth watering! Also, the drinks were top notch and all was very affordable! We came in on a cold night after walking the french quarter, chilled to the bone and the hostess even put a heater by our table! Would love to eat here again!
Great food, ambience, and service

Sylvain is a good restaurant: lovely ambiance, great location, fantastic service, delicious food. The fries with aioli sauce, the cornbread with cayenne butter, and the fresh market fish encrusted in wasabi were our faves. I just have two complaints. First, their portions are very, very small. We actually went straight to another restaurant to eat again when we left. Secondly, they say they are Southern Cuisine, but I feel the concentration is Asian. Nearly every menu item has Asian influence. As I said though, I like Sylvain, and when the mood hits me just right for Southern Cuisine w/ a heavy Asian influence, I’ll be eating this food again.
Ordered crispy pork belly, shrimp, and fries. Barelly enough for two. Pork was just ok, a lot of fat. $13 for 3 shrimp is too much for a place that looks sketchy inside. This place is overrated IMO.
Relaxed atmosphere with excellent service, food and cocktails.
Fascinating fried chicken. The environment and the atmosphere is pleasant.

We had a delicious meal here with high quality ingredients, superb preparation and thoughtful presentation. Try the sweet potato gnocchi. The same purity is reflected in the craft cocktails.  This is the place to try a hurricane.  It’s not the kitschy slushy you might be avoiding.  There’s spacious indoor seating and highly prized outdoor dining as well. The whole package made for a really nice evening.
Horrible loud music and boring menu
Great drinks and quality food. Nice ambiance.
get back out to Sylvain for a nice meal, great service, and much needed outside ambience.
Exceptional food, exceptional cocktails and a great atmosphere! Has outside seating which is a rare gem in New Orleans during covid times!
Great spot.  Great food.  The back courtyard is a gem.  Enjoy

My boyfriend and I dined here a couple of weeks ago for a casual dinner in the courtyard. Service staff were very attentive but not intrusive and the food was on par with our expectations. We plan to come visit again in the future.
american food, yeah, yummy. looking forward to returning with my coworkers. the place has a nice atmosphere.
Great experience, food was outstanding
Best Hurricane in NOLA

Everything about this place is just average. We were there at night and it is super dark inside and out. The staff appeared to be friendly but the food was just average. The music is one reason not to visit. It is super loud and it is kind of grungy with a disco beat, makes you want to order a couple of razor blades for dessert.
Ordered takeout. Food was mediocre and lacked character
American food at this spot - great. I love this place, great food & service. I will probably become a regular. The bill was appropriate for the quality. I can see why they have so many great reviews.
Cornbread hit the spot and service was fast!
Awesome service and food.

I had a good night here.  They were serving late on labor day weekend and it wasnt packed.  I ordered the Brussel Salad and the pork shoulder.  They are both pictured. The atmosphere was pretty nice and the waitresses were responsive.  This meal made me full and Intook a half shoulder home.  The brussel salad was really crunchy.  I was expecting alot of brussel sprouts , but that doesnt seem to be what this dish was.  It was good and I do recommend
Great food and great service!
I never miss Sylvain when I go to NOLA.
The food was good and the service was friendly. And they had the best music playing in the background that we've heard since arriving in the Big Easy.
Great atmosphere and patio sitting available
Wonderful drinks and excellent service!
went on 7/3/20 just after they reopened from COVID.  they did a great job of being safe and making everyone comfortable.  it was really great food and the ambiance is wonderful.

First time there, it was terrible. Outside seating had ants all over the place. So after I moved and being the only black couple there. I sat there for 15 min and watched the staff walk pass me about 15 times. So I got up to say something to the host, turned around and the lady that walked passed us several times was wiping down our table...... They clearly have a problem with black people..... Never again!!!!
The burger with a side salad will do you right. Sit at the bar and share a drink or two with friends. Great quarter spot.

I went here with my partner for his birthday dinner. The mood was so romantic with all the candles throughout the restaurant. We got a seat by the french door looking out and it was amazing. Although a bit pricey, the food was super delicious. Our only suggestion is the music - it's a bit too loud  and interrupts the feel of the restaurant.

I love the Pot de crème, best I've ever had, I also love the cocktails. Unfortunately their entrees leave something to be desired. I expect to love my food at these price points . I would only return for drinks and pot de crème.
The food is very good.  They had their own take on liver pate and corn bread.  Everything was excellent including the service.  And the cocktails!
Truly a unique New Orleans restaurant. Great friendly service.

The food was delicious and well crafted. The staff were all very helpful, and sat us quickly even though they were verg busy. There were two of us and we shared three appetizers and left full and satisfied.
Although everything we ordered was good, the menu was limited and offerings were unique. Meal was a bit pricey for the anount of food we had: $325 inc. wine.
Yummy burgers and fries!
We were seated outside next to a giant and noisy AC condenser. The experience was not the best we hoped for
Everyone who works here, including my friend Aubrey, looks like models. The food & drinks are great too, and there is a gorgeous courtyard.
Excellent service and food with a super New Orleans romantic vibe.

Good food, good service. I had the redfish and it was grilled and seasoned to perfection. Don't miss the cornbread.  For a non-alcoholic drink try the sylvain cola. Everything was very nice and the waiter noticed that I  had left my credit card and he ran out to find me. Above and beyond. Thank you.
Hostess was rude. But Morgan was a sweetheart and took great care of us. She was so nice and accommodating, unlike the hostess. Get a new hostess, she will cost you customers.
This place has very unique atmosphere and they have good cocktails. But the foods are not delicious and the service is a little bit snop.
Didn't like anything and they're overpriced

The food is the star here, though we only shared a couple small items, it was some of the best food we had in New Orleans! I can't find the name on their online menu of what we enjoyed the most, but it had duck and poached eggs. The eggs were perfect, and the duck was so incredibly flavorful! Our drinks were also excellent. The staff is top-notch here, everyone was very attentive from the moment we walked in. There was a slight wait for the courtyard, but we were offered a spot at the bar to wait, and then were able to take our drinks with us once the table opened, and pay for everything together at the end. Our server was on top of everything, and very pleasant! Next time in town, we will absolutely come back!

LOVE LOVE LOVE this place. It was a shame that I couldn’t come here more than once during my stay in New Orleans. Started off with the hurricanes that were made with freshly crushed ice (I had never seen an ice crusher before) and they were delicious. For dinner I paired the chicken sandwich with the Maison Joseph chard and it changed my life. I’ll be dreaming about Sylvain until my next stay in Nola.
Waitress curt not very friendly. Food o.k. not great

We went in with a reservation, they did not care, they said the wait was 45 minutes. But we could go it at the bar. We sat down in the bar area after getting no service for a while we figured something was wrong, so we went to a server and we were told we were not allowed to sit anywhere except on a bar stool. Ok that must be the way of doing things in New Orleans. Unfortunately, at this point we run out of time and we had to leave hungry. But wait didn't we have a reservation? It seems they don't care and deserve a zero star, what else can I give them?
Great burger, great sweetbreads
Came here for for a small bite.   The gulf shrimp is delicious.
Great vibe, great menu, great drinks. Service is a bit slow but the food is worth the wait.

We stumbled upon Sylvain looking for somewhere laid back for a quick mid-morning meal. We sat at the bar and while we were initially going to resist the cocktails, watching the bartenders create these incredible masterpieces proved irresistible- so we ended up trying quite a few of the cocktails they offered.  The food was just perfect and the atmosphere was very hip -but at the same time, extremely welcoming.  And the cocktails just topped it off. I can't think of a single thing that could be improved here. Would love to try dinner here... the next time we are all in town.
Amazing, our server Carl gave us great suggestions!
Pretty good restaurant, I enjoyed the ambiance and the food. The burger was white yummy, and the late was great. Overall, nice for dinner without much fuss.
Loved eating outside here. Food and people  were wonderful
A NOLA gem tucked away down a dark alleyway.  Stumbled across it on a late night out.
Great service and cool vibe. We ate here twice while in town for only 4 nights it was so good. Hands down the best burger I’ve had anywhere.
Such a great meal! Alex provided great service too. I work at an upscale restaurant in Chicago, and she does a better job than I do. I recommend this place highly.
Lovely alfresco dining area in the back, very romantic and quiet. Delicious fresh seafood and great selection of cocktails. This was our first restaurant in New Orleans and we were impressed :)
Great brunch place, nice atmosphere, slow service though
The courtyard was cool. Service was very good. Cocktails were tasty. The food was overpriced and underwhelming.

What a beautiful romantic place. We enjoyed our 10 year anniversary dinner here and couldn't have picked a better place. The  candle lighting is creating a magical atmosphere and so does the choice of music. The hostess was so friendly and our waiter took great care of us. The food was fantastic. Sylvains came recommended to us by a New Orleans native and I'm so glad we did it. Big bonus they have something for every budget. So take your date and have a magical night.
Very good food and cocktails - the crispy pork shoulder with collard greens and grits was stupendous!
Yummy food. Great vibe and service. Really enjoyed it.
Delicious champagne cocktails and their chicken sandwich is amazing.
Quaint place. We just stopped in for a drink. Bartender was awesome and my brandy milk punch was excellent. A hungover member of our party said the Corpse Reviver gave her some relief.
Great atmosphere, service, and food. Small menu. Nice quality find away from the crowds.

I love the people that works there , they make you feel like you belong here . This is where the family is . And the owner OMG he is the most nicest person you could ever meet. The food makes you come back for more, they plating is nice I'll take all my friends here when they come in town that's how good the prices are....  I promise you your going to love it.
I've been here twice on two separate trips and would come back everytime I'm in New Orleans. One of the best places to eat in the country
Nice ambience

I had dinner here and all the food was so great. The sampler (I don’t remember the exact name) is a must go. Also, the fried pork shoulder was pretty good too. I would definitely come to this place again if I visit New Orleans again.

(Translated by Google) Well done and good food. Music played a little loud. Friendly staff. The suitable prices  (Original) Cuisine bien faite et bonne. Musique diffusée un peu forte. Personnel aimable. Les prix convenables

My family came down to NOLA for a graduation and we had reservations here for dinner. The food was fantastic. We ordered the shaved Brussels Sprouts for an appetizer and I couldn’t believe how delicious they were.  I ordered the hamburger and fries for my dinner and it was the best burger I have ever had. The service was stellar and our server Jacob went above and beyond to make sure we had a special night. We were raving about our meals so much to Jacob that we actually got a visit from the chef, J.R, at our table to thank us for the compliments. The atmosphere was very relaxed and comfortable. I highly recommend coming here and I can’t wait to return.
This review goes out to the manager which handled a situation tonight with such grace and care. All management should be ran this way.

I haven't tasted the food their yet but I always pass by and Its this guy, I think his name is Mr. William. His such a cool and funny guy. His always working so hard. I often wonder, do he ever take a break. He always offer me to come sit and eat.. William says, Mrs. Krayola our food is fresh and better than any food you ever had.   One day, I just might take him up on his offer.
Loud, overpriced with a long wait.  Almost sent out for a pizza while waiting.  After eating, I was sorry that I didn't.

Lovely environment! I loved the dim lighting and overall feel. It was great for a date night while in town. Allergy information wasn’t posted on the menu but our waitress went above and beyond to accommodate my allergy once she was informed of it- so that was amazing. The food was good, but I gave four stars because I could see myself returning based on the environment and drinks over the food. All in all I would recommend!

My only reason for the second star is the house made hot sauce - which I only found out about because our server recommended to another table. Otherwise it would be a one star. Just seems like a trendy front to another overpriced  tourist trap. The small plates were good - nothing very exciting. The ambiance was nice, but we were seated in a breezeway and clearly not cool enough for our wannabe DJ server to give us any attention. We spent a lot of time waiting, the cocktails were good but not amazing. Nothing on the brunch menu was appealing and we ended up with a few small plates. The homemade hot sauce was very good but the rest really fell so short of expectations. There is so much potential for this place. Maybe we caught it at a bad time but we literally found a place down the street to eat after finishing our meal.

Sylvains has the best service, food, and atmosphere in New Orleans. It was so great we went twice. Alex took care of us our first night. She was so chill, calming, and made us truly take in the restaurant. Alex’s food and drink suggestions blew us away. She also treated us with quick service without feeling rushed. We enjoyed our time so much she introduced us Carl, who would take care of us our next night (since she wouldn’t be working). Carl was phenomenal and made us feel so welcomed! He had such a passion for the restaurant and New Orleans. His energy made us feel so excited to be back and thankful to find Sylvains. The vibe was true New Orleans feel without the stuffy or trashy sides of the city - a “you do you” atmosphere where you are treated like family and royalty all at the same time. Something I never thought possible... #onlyinneworleans Thank you for a dining experience of a lifetime.

(Translated by Google) Overpriced food for what is served at the end, but delicious and good cocktails  (Original) Etwas überteuertes Essen für das was am Ende serviert wird, aber lecker und gute Cocktails
Best ever, hands down!!!  Food, service, setting!!!  A must if you're visiting NOLA!

I am so happy to return after 3 years.  Came to town to see U2 in 2017 and went to Sylvains with a friend. We loved it.  When I returned to New Orleans it was on my list to return to. So happy I did.  Everything is on point from the walk way in to the lighting , music , decor. The atmosphere is wonderful.  We ate at the bar both times .  Excellent friendly service.  Great cocktails. Food was tremendous.  The southern charcuterie was fantastic! Cornbread was the best.  The grilled pork shoulder patties were simply delicious.  Treat yourself to their special after dinner drink made from roasted corn puree with mezcal.  Sort of an eggnogish drink.   Really fantastic and completely original.
Delish
Dark, classic bar with excellent staff and marvelous cocktails. Nice outdoor patio in back to eat in; very good, simple food. Recommended!
Good food good service
So minus the long wait which was to be expected on a Saturday night the food was amazing! Well worth the wait. The cocktails are also delicious if you find yourself waiting
Very nice restaurant with good food and reasonable prices. Nice romantic atmosphere with candle lit surroundings. Service is excellent too. Can’t ask for more.
Hurricane made here is sooooo good , Food is tasty Atmosphere trendy
This place defines eating and drinking in Nola for us
Went for brunch on a Saturday. Super nice & attentive wait staff, great eclectic menu and food, beautiful restaurant. Would recommend.
The atmosphere and food were great!

This place is just fantastic. At first I didn't want to go inside because from outside you can really tell how beautiful is the restaurant.  After reading all the good reviews I decided to finally go inside.  The service was fast and good. Everything was cooked to perfection and beautifully garnished. This was one of my best meals during my stay.  I would definitely be back and I recommend this restaurant to anyone who is looking for excellent food and service.

The bartenders were awesome - obviously very skilled at their craft. They were also very personable and friendly. If this were solely a bar, it would be a 5* bar. But, but they sell food and lots of people go there to get something to eat. The menu is small and limited to things that probably seemed fancy in ‘93. The kitchen is in a constant state of being backed up.  And then, after you wait 40 minutes for a chicken sandwich, you are handed a some deep fried chicken breast on a cold bun and soggy fries.  The fries were particularly offensive because they were obviously cooked in oil that wasn’t hot enough. So, they were hot to the touch, but soaked in oil and not crispy.  Bottom line - if you want a drink and cool ambience, this is a great place. But, eat elsewhere.
Great bar and service

Was never seated for our reservation...walked out after waiting more than an hour after our rez, there was an open table of 4 directly next to us the ENTIRE time we waited. After inquiring about our table we mentioned that we planned a quick meal and were told that because of that we were not welcome to a table at all for the rest of the evening, immediately left to a different much better restaurant.

So sad!  Used to be such fantastic food and service to match.  Don’t bother anymore with so many awesome options in town this one and their management deserves to be buried alive by all the awesome options around town!  Chef used be so good, write home to mom kind of deal.  Not anymore it’s expensive food that tastes cheap and the overall experience cheapens it even further.  Half (blank) trained service staff that have no clue how to treat people.  In my mind 5 star reflects food and service and both failed this trip!  I would say 3 food and 2 service.  Wow sorry it’s slipped I just hope the top of the food chain can save this one before it’s gone, great location.

A cozy spot with intriguing food and beverages away from the madness if Bourbon Street.  My Ratatouille with rice was lovely, and the housemade cola was marvellous.  Ask for Dawn, she'll get you what you need.
(Translated by Google) The food is good, too much delay in serving it.  (Original) La comida es buena, demasiada la demora en servirla.

(Translated by Google) Overrated restaurant! Between the difficulty of having a table, the wait for the service and the dishes too salty ... This restaurant is much too pretentious. Incidentally, if you have a hungry wolf, do not take pasta bolo because the portion is very minimal. I put a star for the atmosphere of the place.  (Original) Restaurant surcoté ! Entre la difficulté d'avoir une table, l'attente du service et les plats beaucoup trop salés... Ce restaurant est beaucoup trop prétentieux. Au passage, si vous avez une faim de loup, ne prenez pas les pâtes bolo car la portion est très minime. Je mets une étoile pour l'ambiance des lieux.
Well i tried the brussel sprouts salad and hamburger... And everything was good they need more lighting in the place it was kind of dark. Waitress was nice and helpful
Loved it...! Service great as is the food..
Gluten free options available. This place is very romantic and New Orleans. I loved it. A great pick for a date night!
Great food, service and atmosphere

Good not great. The venue and vibe of Sylvain was very cozy and charming. The was a short wait time and they allow you to order drinks while you wait. A very nice choice of refreshing drinks. The location is right in the middle of everything but it’s on the quieter side of things. We were able to get seated inside which is a nice relief from the heat. The food just happened to miss the mark slightly. Also, and this may be commonplace in the French Quarter, there was a ginormous roach walking on the wall right by me.
Slow service..Food not great

This place had excellent charm, food, and cocktails! As of Oct 2019, they do not have a gluten free menu, but the staff was very knowledgeable about gluten free options. Imho, this was a must stop for visitors!
Great atmosphere nice costumer service
Great atmosphere and the food and cocktails were delightful.
The kitchen is open until midnight. If you need to get your second wind, wander over, and have the fried chicken sandwich and a cocktail.  Highly recommended!
Amazing food!
*delicious*

(Translated by Google) Great kitchen, very nice staff! Small card, but everything fresh and 1a quality. A visit will be worth it in any case.  (Original) Tolle Küche, sehr nettes Personal! Kleine Karte, aber alles frisch und 1a-Qualität. Ein Besuch lohnt sich in jedem Fall.
Great mixed drinks
Fantastic food and soundtrack to match. Try to expertly crafted Mexican Firing Squad cocktail.
Delicious food, great cocktails and overall vibe.
Great location. Cozy dining room. Attentive service. Did a business dinner here and was not disappointed.
Great local food. Leveled up beyond anything in the quarter.
Excellent food, great staff, and cool environment.  Added bonus... we got to enjoy 'maggot brain' over the PA during brunch at the bar.
Great

Great food, good cocktails, excellent atmosphere, friendly service. Not much more you could ask for. Starter highlights: cornbread and grilled shrimp. I had the house made parpadelle bolognese and loved it. Chocolate pot de creme to end the meal was ridiculously decadent. Portion size a plus . . . for normal human beings. Recommend a visit.
Exceptional service and great food
Very cute place with good food and fancy drinks. Service was good. Portion sizes are on the small side.
LOVE LOVE LOVE SYLVAIN.  THE SERVICE, THE ATMOSPHERE, AND THE DELICIOUS FOOD.  PLEASE GET THE ANTIPASTI PLATE AND THE BRUSSEL SPROUT SALAD....I CRAVE DAILY.
Chicken was very sour and a little bit on the dry side. Pan-Fried Pork Shoulder was delicious!
Food was fantastic!!  End to end the meal and drinks were great.  Charcuterie plate was a home run.
Amazing food and service
Very quaint, out of the way spot for an intimate lunch or dinner, or just drinks
Tasty food for a good price and friendly staff. Music was very loud though ... couldn't hear my own words. Some people like that apparantly ...

(Translated by Google) All good, even cocktails. Price aligned to the position (full French quarter). A bit dark and noisy inside, we were not lucky enough to dine out. Air conditioning with cannon as normally in the USA  (Original) Tutto buono, anche i cocktail. Prezzo allineato alla posizione (pieno quartiere francese). Un po' buio e rumoroso all'interno, non abbiamo avuto la fortuna di cenare fuori. Aria condizionata a cannone come di norma negli USA
Food is not bad but way overpriced for burger, chicken sandwich, and flank steak - with French fries.

I had a great solo dinner here, the food and cocktails were both awesome and at a good price point. Not a touristy feeling place, this is somewhere I would eat if I lived here. I went in planning to do the COOLinary, but the daily special sounded too appealing and I am glad I made the switch.
This place is great.
(Translated by Google) The only dark point is the difficulty of having a table 🤗  (Original) Le seul point noire est la difficulté d'y avoir une table 🤗
A must when NOLA
(Translated by Google) On the terrace between the toilet and the kitchen, not easy to enjoy the dishes.  (Original) En terrasse entre les toilettes et la cuisine, pas facile d’apprécier les plats.
Birthday celebration! Fun time and the bartender was great! My friend Genorie remembered meeting him in Chattanooga!
Great food and friendly staff.
Good food and great service!
Great food. Great cocktails. Casual. (Dropping one start because they need to tweak their playlist)
One of the best burgers I've had in a while. Cocktails are really good as well. Came here during Hurricane Barry, and was glad they were open and had amazing foods!
Every time we go we have a great time and can't wait to come back occasionally more than once a day.
Death & Co pop up bar at Tails of the Cocktail was a challenge but the staff worked hard to ensure everyone had a great time.
Cool atmosphere, very laid back, relaxing. Service was good, food delicious.
Very yummy, great atmosphere, beautiful courtyard, friendly staff. A great place to eat.
Amazing fries and sub zero AC!
Carl was an excellent server and the staff made us feel at home. We sat in the back patio where they really installed a swamp cooler and had big umbrellas to block the sun!

Looked interesting online, decided to try it out.  Probably should have made a reservation, but the managed to fit us in.  Food, drinks and atmosphere were great.  Reminded my wife and I of a southern version of Staple and Fancy (Seattle).
Crisp trout was superb

In town for business and found Sylvain on Google.  Looked cool so took a chance and made a reservation for 4 online.  OMG, best meal I've had in recent memory.  Do not miss this place!!  Wicked cool atmosphere, great service and the pricing was very reasonable.
Friendly service with attention to detail. Best roast chicken I have ever had. My wife's handmade pasta Bolognese was delicious as well!

This restaurant is one of my favorites!! So thankful for the staff that works here. They have a great selection of cocktails that keep you coming back as well as food that can make even the biggest foodie keep coming back.  I wouldn’t  say to get any particular item on the menu because every time I come I get something different and it hasn’t failed me yet!! I really hope u enjoy the atmosphere as much as I do, u won’t be disappointed I promise!
Is amazing experience
5 star food unique and not too fancy
40 minutes and the food never came while the other tables were getting served. The manager did come out to apologize so that was nice, would not come back though.

In New Oleans looking for a place to eat off the beaten path.  Talked to some nice locals and they suggested Sylvain.  They say it was a smaller menu but delicious and they were not wrong.  I have the Pan fried pork shoulder and it was awesome.   It was so good that I decided I had to have the desert.  It was a berry something pound cake.  I was not as excited.  Tasted like it had been in the refrigerator for a day or two.

We would've never found this place if we didn't know it was there. We absolutely loved our stay. This is a place that we will recommend to all our friends. Try the appetizers and the wait staff will take care of you!

A beautiful restaurant both inside and out, but a bit difficult to find from the street. Our Lyft driver was as confused as we were when dropping us off at the place according to the map. After looking in some windows however, we had success and were promptly seated in the courtyard.  We opted for four small plates and were not disappointed. Their selections are unusual and creative, but delectable. The white gazpacho with grapes was heavenly and beyond compare.  Cocktails were good, service was great, and the ambiance was near perfect.
Wow! Delish!! Perfect.
Great food exquisite wine and my first Schlitz. The service was impeccable the ambiance was awsome. A jewel of the quarter.
Great food, ambiance and service
Best cocktails we've had in New Orleans!
Cool space with solid cocktails.
It was the best meal I've ever had in my life. If you value and seek beauty and personal fulfillment in life, then please go to this restaurant.
Good food, the pork shoulder was great, nice wine list, service was friendly.
Excellent pork shoulder
The bartenders here are awesome. The vibe is chill. Def a gem.
Great service.  Awesome food
Best dinner in NOLA! Romantic with an exciting menu. Go hungry and adventurous!
Good, well mixed cocktails and tasty food.
This was a super cute modern take on southern  cuisine, ask to sit outside if you can.  The only bad thing i can say is that the bathroom  was busy

We stopped there yesterday for dinner, had the fried oysters, the beef cheeks, cornbread and the chicken sandwich. There is something really special about traditional French Quarter restaurants that are in 250 year old buildings with the original architecture intact. You can choose between patio or inside service. We went for Sunday brunch and it was amazing. The best shrimp and grits ever and they had a cabbage salad that I could not believe was so good. The general manager Ali was our server and she was so kind and cordial. My new favorite restaurant in New Orleans.

Absolutely phenomenal cocktail menu (try the Southern Slang, the Airmail, or the Lazarus), and a fabulous brunch. Exquisite take on classic Louisiana favorites. The duck & dirty rice is awesome, the sandwiches are hefty and delicious. The appetizer menu is just heavenly. The green goddess dressing is perfect on fried oysters. The duck confit in satsuma sauce is delicious. And if they are serving the gulf fish crudo, snag it like there's no tomorrow! My lans, I have just made myself very, very hungry...

Really solid restaurant experience for the French Quarter. Dishes were executed well and service was attentive. We enjoyed fried oysters (so delicately breaded and fried), shrimp and grits (a classic), duck and more. If this restaurant were elsewhere, not sure it would stand out as much. But it’s not elsewhere. It’s in the French Quarter and it’s a must in the French Quarter. For a moment inside or on the back patio, you forget your in the smelly mess of the Quarter. Seek it out and be grateful.

The last time we were in New Orleans, we were let down (they have always been one of our favorite places). This time they out done themselves. Our starters were off the chain good and appropriately sized. The entrees were perfect. I had the hanger steak, which for a cheaper cut of meat was great. They did not over do the preparation on the meat and let it shine on it's on. It came with fries, which at first was a disappointment.  That soon went away. The fries were great and a perfect complement. My wife got their special, which was a seared duck breast with duck dirty rice. It was amazingly delicious.  It was garnished with pickled bell peppers (mostly red). That complimented the rice perfectly.  For dessert I got the panna cotta, my wife got the pot de creme. The panna cotta (spelling) was delicious.  The pot de creme was decadent.  You literally needed to ask forgiveness between each bite it was so good. If you are in New Orleans, treat yourself to this place. You will be glad you did.
